  {
    "file": "src/Components/Web/src/Forms/DisplayName.cs",
    "line": 46,
    "severity": "high",
    "description": "The _previousFieldAccessor field and expression reference comparison (For != _previousFieldAccessor) is a compliance violation and functional bug. In Blazor, inline lambda expressions (e.g., For=\"@(() => model.Property)\") create new expression objects on every render, so this reference-equality check always evaluates to true and never short-circuits. More critically, when ExpressionMemberAccessor caches are cleared during hot reload (via ClearCache), the component's own _displayName is NOT refreshed because the expression reference comparison prevents re-evaluation. This causes stale display names after hot reload. The fix is to remove the _previousFieldAccessor field and outer if-block entirely, always calling GetDisplayName(For) and relying on ExpressionMemberAccessor._displayNameCache (keyed by MemberInfo, which IS stable) for performance, with only the inner display-name-change check gating re-renders.",
    "fix_applied": true
  },
  {
    "file": "src/Components/Web/src/Forms/ExpressionMemberAccessor.cs",
    "line": 15,
    "severity": "high",
    "description": "The _memberInfoCache (ConcurrentDictionary<Expression, MemberInfo>) uses Expression as dictionary key with default reference equality. Since Expression objects are not reused across Blazor render cycles (new lambda objects created each render for inline lambdas), this cache never hits in typical usage, causing the dictionary to grow unboundedly — a memory leak in long-running applications. Additionally, the ClearCache method unnecessarily clears _memberInfoCache (which is already effectively empty due to cache misses). The fix is to remove _memberInfoCache entirely and evaluate expressions directly in GetMemberInfo on each call. The meaningful caching is already handled by _displayNameCache (keyed by MemberInfo, which is a stable singleton per member in .NET reflection). ClearCache is updated to only clear _displayNameCache.",
    "fix_applied": true
  }
]

